exif:ImageDescription: Constructing the Colony. While existing villages were adapted for the settlement, a number of new structures were set up for new community. For example, The Baldwin Home for Boys was overseen by Catholic Brothers of the Order of Saint Francis. An entire complex of structures once stood at the base of the cliffs, including the grotto pictured above.
